# Local overrides for the Vite dev server. NOT committed (gitignored).
#
# Point the FE at the production ALB instead of the local docker stack.
#
# Why: the local docker server pushes recommend jobs onto the SHARED SQS queue,
# but ECS workers push results into ElastiCache (their Redis), not the docker
# Redis. So the local server times out on /recommend even when ECS workers
# successfully produced products. Routing the FE through the ALB removes the
# cross-Redis split — the ECS server reads its own Redis, picks up the
# ECS-worker result, and returns it cleanly.
#
# Set blank or remove this file to revert to docker server.
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://hyperpersona-alb-928612666.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com
